WEBVTT

00:00:06.854 --> 00:00:17.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah shows sincere hospitality.
He cares for all without partiality.

00:00:17.437 --> 00:00:23.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He gives both rain and sun,
withholding these from none;

00:00:23.604 --> 00:00:29.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He fills our hearts
with food and good cheer.

00:00:29.437 --> 00:00:40.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Whenever we show favor to lowly ones,
We imitate our God as beloved sons.

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:46.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our Father will repay
the goodness we display,

00:00:46.270 --> 00:00:51.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our kindness
that is truly sincere.

00:00:54.687 --> 00:00:59.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We never know the good
that may come about

00:00:59.979 --> 00:01:05.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we see those in need
and we help them out.

00:01:05.520 --> 00:01:16.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Though strangers they may be, in hospitality,
We lend a hand to care for their needs.

00:01:16.729 --> 00:01:22.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Like Lydia of old, we say:
‘Be my guest.’

00:01:22.479 --> 00:01:28.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When they come to our home,
they find peace and rest.

00:01:28.312 --> 00:01:34.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our Father is aware
of all those ev’rywhere,

00:01:34.145 --> 00:01:39.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who imitate his merciful deeds.

